      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GRAVITY MONELLI (7) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 4.5 lengths win at this track in a handy 34.94. Outside box to overcome but in form and has the ability. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Can continue on his winning ways. AURORA'S IMAGE (8) collided with another runner and finished a well held 5 lengths fourth (28.08) last time in a Novice race at Mandurah over 488m. Has the ability and looks a key chance. RAMIREZ MONELLI (1) could manage only fifth over 520m at this track last time when gave a start and was beaten 6 lengths in a OPEN (30.49). Likely to enjoy the staying trip for the first time. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. QUEEN GODDESS (3) was well supported last time but could only manage second (35.26), beaten 4.5 lengths. Overdue and is among the main hopes.",
